    Good day out!
    Camden market has a buzzing atmosphere. It’s a maze of vintage shops, leather goods, accessories, books, record shops, toys and food kiosks all situated in old stables. Here you will also find the Amy Winehouse Statue which I’m a big fan of and took multiple photos. I would plan to spend a good few hours here as there is so many shops and stalls and things to see but it’s time and money well spent but it can be an expensive day out.

GlobeTrotting621671
Witney, UK47 contributions
Definitely worth a visit - we love it
Oct 2024 • Family
We love Camden - best market in London. There are loads of independent food vendors with everything you could think of and lots of shops. The food queues aren’t bad if you time it well - aim to be eating before 12!
We find the shops quite similar with lots offering identical products but it’s worth a visit and the food more than makes up for it. If you have the choice of Camden or borough and you want food to eat (rather than market produces e.g cheeses etc) - I would 100% choose Camden, it’s also much less crowded and much more open!

David
Dundee, UK68 contributions
Great place (visit here instead of Borough market)
Oct 2024 • Couples
Visited on a recent trip to London.

It was busy however easy to navigate and the shops and food stalls were all accessible apart from the ones clearly paying TikTok “influencers” to advertise on their behalf.

We ate at a good few and compared to the borough market it was a far better experience and plenty more options at reasonable prices.

The humble crumble stall was fantastic and a must visit whilst the Tacos and noodles we ate were also very good.

We had a few drinks in bars as well and the staff and prices were decent enough for London.

lori1019
Chicago, Illinois200 contributions
Fun Place to Wander Around
Oct 2024 • Couples
Make sure that after you exit the tube, you walk down the street past all of the junky shops. This is NOT the actual market. Once down the street by the bridge, you can meander through stalls of artisan items and food. There are some stalls with obviously crappy jewelry, but most are really a fun assortment of items and art. Lots of food stalls to choose from. Not too many places to sit down and eat, but you can find one. After we walked around, we took a London Waterbus narrow boat ride down the canal. Made for a really nice day.
